titles: A list of the names of the Irish prisoners, now lodg'd in So-ho-square, London. Being the several lords, generals, collonels, lieutenant-collonels, majors, captains, &c. which were taken prisoners at the several actions of Ballymore, Athlone and Aghrim; and lately (by sea) brought from Dublin to England.
notes: Reproduction of the original in the National Library of Scotland.
